        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Element_Radio elements lack ids for javascript access\n\nI tested this on today's trunk and 1.5 release\n\nCreate a subform:\n{code}[subfrm]\nelements.subfrm.name = \"0\";\nelements.subfrm.type = \"radio\";\nelements.subfrm.options.belongsTo = \"subfrm\";\nelements.subfrm.options.disableLoadDefaultDecorators = \"true\";\nelements.subfrm.options.decorators.ViewHelper.decorator = \"ViewHelper\";\nelements.subfrm.options.value = \"true\";\nelements.subfrm.options.multiOptions.true = \"\";\nelements.subfrm.options.multiOptions.false = \"\";\n{code}\n\nAfter assigning it in the view, print it in the view\n{code}\n<?=$this->form->subfrm?>\n{code}\n\nThe result it:\n{code}\n<label style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n<input name=\"subfrm[0]\" value=\"true\" checked=\"checked\" type=\"radio\">\n<\/label>\n<br>\n<label style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n<input name=\"subfrm[0]\" value=\"false\" type=\"radio\">\n<\/label>\n{code}\n\nExpected result\n{code}\n<label style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n<input name=\"subfrm[0]\" id=\"subfrm-0-true\" value=\"true\" checked=\"checked\" type=\"radio\">\n<\/label>\n<br>\n<label style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">\n<input name=\"subfrm[0]\" id=\"subfrm-0-false\" value=\"false\" type=\"radio\">\n<\/label>\n{code}\n\nA quick and dirty fix would be:\nEditing a part of Zend_View_Helper_FormRadio to:\n{code}\n\/\/ Wrap the radios in labels\n            $radio = '<label'\n                    . $this->_htmlAttribs($label_attribs) . '>'\n                    . (('prepend' == $labelPlacement) ? $opt_label : '')\n                    . '<input type=\"' . $this->_inputType . '\"'\n                    . ' id=\"' . preg_replace('\/\\[([^\\]]+)\\]\/', '-$1', $name) .'-'. $this->view->escape($opt_value) . '\"'\n                    . ' name=\"' . $name . '\"'\n                    . ' value=\"' . $this->view->escape($opt_value) . '\"'\n                    . $checked\n                    . $disabled\n                    . $this->_htmlAttribs($attribs) \n                    . $endTag\n                    . (('append' == $labelPlacement) ? $opt_label : '')\n                    . '<\/label>';\n{code}\n\nI don't think its intended to be fixed there however.\nI haven't digged into the id attaching for textfields etc enough to provide a better fix, maybe i'll do that later."
        },
